entry.title: [Files app] Make `GuestOsSharePath` depend on `VolumeManager`
entry.content:
The `GuestOsSharePath` currently registers as an observer of

`VolumeManager` in it's constructor and de-registers in its Shutdown

method. It's possible that `VolumeManager` is destructed before

`GuestOsSharePath` and in the Shutdown method it then tries to create a

`VolumeManager` instance.



This adds the DependsOn explicitly in the `GuestOsSharePathFactory` and

adds a new method to just find the existing `VolumeManager` instead of

trying to create a new one. The former is probably not strictly

necessary given the DependsOn, but can't hurt to ensure a new one isn't

created.



Furthermore this ensures the observer is removed from the `DriveFsHost`

and updates to use `base::ScopedObservation` instead. Given the

dependency on `DriveFsHost` this also ensures a `DependsOn` is added

for `drive::DriveIntegrationService` as well.



Bug: b/297425959

entry.title: Use `float` for `tilt_x` and `tilt_y` before UI event creation
entry.content:
The precision of `altitude_angle` and `azimuth_angle` relies on `tilt_x` and `tilt_y` to be a double. Since `tilt_x` and `tilt_y` are rounded once the DOM event is created, we should be using doubles before then to ensure the previous statement. Since OSes usually provide tilts with float precision, we restrict the values to floats.

entry.title: Remove gfx::HDRMetadata from cc::TargetColorParams
entry.content:
This is towards taking cc::TargetColorParams out of the

cc::GpuImageDecodeCache key.



The gfx::HDRMetadata is extra information about an image, analogous to

the ICC profile. It does not belong in cc::TargetColorParams, which is

information about the color space that content is to be rasterized

into.



Remove gfx::HDRMetadata from cc::TargetColorParams, and place it on

cc::PaintImage.



At present, cc::PaintImage can also get the HDR metadata from its

cc::ImageHeaderMetadata. It may be preferable to move this at some

point.
